{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-30T21:22:07.034Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file__write_file_1780176127032_0","parameters":{"file_path":"papers/README.md","content":"# Downloaded Papers\n\n1. **InterPLM: Discovering Interpretable Features in Protein Language Models via Sparse Autoencoders** (2024)\n   - Authors: Elana Simon, James Y. Zou\n   - ArXiv: 2412.12101\n   - Why relevant: Main framework for discovering novel latent features in ESM-2.\n\n2. **From Mechanistic Interpretability to Mechanistic Biology: Training, Evaluating, and Interpreting Sparse Autoencoders on Protein Language Models** (2025)\n   - Authors: Etowah Adams, et al.\n   - ArXiv: 2406.04093\n   - Why relevant: Directly addresses using SAEs to generate hypotheses for unknown biological mechanisms.\n\n3. **Evolutionary-scale prediction of atomic-level protein structure with a language model** (2022)\n   - Authors: Lin et al. (Meta AI)\n   - ArXiv: 2207.03061\n   - Why relevant: Foundational paper for ESM-2, the base model for the interpretability studies.\n"}}
